  "Gadolinium has one extra proton that forces an electron into the 5d orbital": "",
  "A half-filled 4f subshell (4f⁷) provides extra stability due to exchange energy, making this configuration lower in energy": "",
  "Half-filled and fully filled subshells are exceptionally stable due to exchange energy. Gadolinium achieves a half-filled 4f⁷ configuration by promoting one electron to 5d, similar to how chromium achieves 3d⁵ 4s¹.": "",
  "An analytical chemist uses atomic emission spectroscopy to identify unknown metals in a water sample. The instrument detects emission lines matching those of mercury. If a mercury atom has an electron excited from the 6s to the 7s orbital, what must happen for the emission line to be produced?": "",
